<Class name="CM_Rail" id="2a2147ce-9700-4650-8ffe-69516e93dc5a">
    <superclass name="CM_TerminalArea"/>
    <persistentAllowed/>
    <sharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassPersistentAllowed/>
    <subclassSharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassTransientAllowed/>
    <transientAllowed/>
    <text>Is responsible for looking after the rail rake areas defined in the system.
Looks after its graphical representation.
Wagon numbers are input along with a wagon rake position.
Wagon controllers (and their available locations) are then created from this list.
A RailRake is created and bound to the first and last location controller in each rake
The location dictionary is then created by iterating over each rake and related
location controllers.</text>
    <DbClassMap file="location"/>
